---

CHANGE 1 — Fix deprecated datetime.utcnow()
In app/models.py, replace:
  default=datetime.utcnow
with:
  default=lambda: datetime.now(timezone.utc)
Add `from datetime import timezone` to the imports.

---

CHANGE 2 — Extract shared _is_light_mode_enabled() to app/utils.py
Both sentiment.py and embeddings.py contain an identical _is_light_mode_enabled() 
function. 
- Create a new file app/utils.py with a single shared version of this function.
- Remove the duplicate from sentiment.py and embeddings.py.
- Import it from app.utils in both files.

---

CHANGE 3 — Centralize model config into app/config.py
- Create app/config.py using Pydantic BaseSettings.
- Move these constants into it: SENTIMENT_MODEL, ZERO_SHOT_MODEL, EMBEDDING_MODEL_NAME,
  DEFAULT_OLLAMA_MODEL, EMOTION_LABELS, POSITIVE_WORDS, NEGATIVE_WORDS.
- Replace all usages in sentiment.py, embeddings.py, and insights.py with imports 
  from app.config.
- Support overriding all model names via environment variables 
  (e.g. JMT_SENTIMENT_MODEL, JMT_OLLAMA_MODEL).

---

CHANGE 4 — Add input validation for journal text length
In app/main.py, on the POST /entries endpoint:
- Add a Pydantic field_validator that raises a 422 error if the text is empty or 
  exceeds 2000 characters.
- Add a helper that truncates text to 400 words before passing to HuggingFace 
  pipelines (which have a 512-token limit), logging a warning if truncation occurs.

---

CHANGE 5 — Refactor FAISSCache into a proper class
In app/main.py, replace the plain _faiss_cache dict + _faiss_cache_lock globals 
with a small FAISSCache class that encapsulates:
- The index, id_map, and count fields.
- A threading.Lock internally.
- Methods: needs_rebuild(current_count), update(index, id_map, count), get().
Keep existing rebuild logic intact, just move it to use the class.

---

CHANGE 6 — Add missing tests for embeddings edge cases
In tests/test_sentiment_and_insights.py (or a new test file), add:
- test_deserialize_embedding_with_corrupt_bytes: pass random bytes of wrong length, 
  assert ValueError is raised.
- test_build_faiss_index_empty: call build_faiss_index([]) and assert it returns 
  (None, []) or raises gracefully.
- test_generate_embedding_empty_string: assert ValueError is raised.

---

CHANGE 7 — Add auth middleware tests
In tests/test_api_integration.py, add tests for require_local_or_token:
- test_remote_request_without_token_returns_403: mock request.client.host to a 
  non-local IP with no LOCAL_API_TOKEN env var set, assert 403.
- test_remote_request_with_valid_token_passes: set LOCAL_API_TOKEN env var, send 
  request with matching x-api-token header, assert it passes through.
- test_local_request_always_passes: mock host as 127.0.0.1, assert no auth required.

---

CHANGE 8 — Consolidate conftest.py fixtures
Currently test DB setup logic is duplicated between conftest.py and 
test_api_integration.py. 
- Move the shared test DB engine, TestingSessionLocal, and override_get_db fixture 
  into conftest.py as pytest fixtures with appropriate scope.
- Remove the duplicated setup from test_api_integration.py and use the shared 
  fixtures instead.

---

CHANGE 9 — Add CSV export endpoint
In app/main.py, add:
  GET /entries/export?format=csv
- Streams all entries as a CSV file using StreamingResponse.
- Columns: date, sentiment_label, sentiment_score, top emotion, raw_text.
- Set Content-Disposition header to attachment; filename="journal_export.csv".
In dashboard.py, add a "Download Export" button in the sidebar that calls this 
endpoint and triggers a file download.

---

CHANGE 10 — Add PUT /entries/{date} update endpoint
In app/main.py, add:
  PUT /entries/{date}
- Accepts a new text body.
- Re-runs analyze_entry and generate_embedding on the new text.
- Updates the existing DB record (sentiment, emotions, embedding, raw_text).
- Rebuilds FAISS index cache after update.
- Returns the updated entry.
Add a corresponding test in test_api_integration.py.

---

CHANGE 11 — Add mood calendar heatmap to dashboard
In dashboard.py, add a new "Calendar View" tab or section:
- Fetch all entries from GET /entries.
- Build a Plotly calendar heatmap (go.Heatmap) showing sentiment_score per day 
  across a full year grid (rows = weeks, columns = days of week).
- Color scale: red (negative) → yellow (neutral) → green (positive).
- Show date and sentiment label on hover.

