CHANGE 13 — Add .env.example file
Create a .env.example file in the project root documenting all supported env vars:
  LOCAL_API_TOKEN=        # Token for non-local API access (min 16 chars recommended)
  OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3     # Ollama model to use for insights
  JMT_LIGHT_MODE=auto     # auto | true | false — skip ML models in light mode
  JMT_SENTIMENT_MODEL=    # Override HuggingFace sentiment model
  JMT_OLLAMA_MODEL=       # Override Ollama model name
  SAFE_MODE=0             # Set to 1 to disable remote write endpoints
Add a note in README.md pointing users to .env.example.

---

CHANGE 14 — Add LOCAL_API_TOKEN minimum length warning at startup
In app/main.py, inside the lifespan async context manager (startup section):
- After loading LOCAL_API_TOKEN from env, check if its length is between 1 and 15.
- If so, log a warning: 
  "WARNING: LOCAL_API_TOKEN is set but shorter than 16 characters. 
   Use a longer token for better security."

---

CHANGE 15 — Add per-endpoint concurrency guard for ML inference
In app/main.py:
- Add a threading.Semaphore(3) (or asyncio.Semaphore) named _inference_semaphore.
- Wrap the ML inference calls in POST /entries and POST /search inside the semaphore 
  so at most 3 concurrent inference requests are processed.
- If the semaphore cannot be acquired within 5 seconds, return HTTP 429 Too Many 
  Requests with message "Server is busy, please retry shortly."

---

CHANGE 16 — Add docker-compose.yml
Create a docker-compose.yml at project root with two services:
  api:
    - Builds from a new Dockerfile.api in the project root.
    - Runs: python -m app.main
    - Exposes port 8000.
    - Mounts ./journal.db as a volume.
    - Passes env vars from a .env file.
  dashboard:
    - Builds from a new Dockerfile.dashboard.
    - Runs: streamlit run dashboard.py --server.port 8501
    - Exposes port 8501.
    - Depends on api service.
Also create minimal Dockerfile.api and Dockerfile.dashboard using python:3.11-slim 
as base. Add a note in README.md under a new "Docker Setup" section.

